\t\u003cdiv data-elementor-type=\"wp-post\" data-elementor-id=\"10318\" data-elementor-post-type=\"post\" data-id=\"b8720ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"theme-post-content.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"46cdcab\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eLet’s honor the remarkable Black Americans throughout history with our favorite books. From the 19th century to the Civil Rights Movement to present day, our reading list for Black History Month is one you don’t want to miss.\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"089999e\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3\u003e\u003ci\u003eBending Toward Justice\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"0262730\" data-element_type=\"container\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"4c10571\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"311\" height=\"466\" src=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bending-Toward-Justice-TP.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bending-Toward-Justice-TP.jpg 311w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Bending-Toward-Justice-TP-200x300.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"b5a7f9f\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eThe story of the decades-long fight to bring justice to the victims of the 16th Street Baptist Church bombing, culminating in Sen. Doug Jones’ prosecution of the last living bombers.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/1250353815?tag=macmillan-20\"\u003eAmazon\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/bending-toward-justice-doug-jones/1128477696?ean=9781250353818\"\u003eB\u0026amp;N\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://bookshop.org/p/books/bending-toward-justice-doug-jones/20673840?ean=9781250353818\u0026amp;next=t\u0026amp;affiliate=3214\"\u003eBookshop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"37623a3\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3\u003e\u003ci\u003eResist\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"d399998\" data-element_type=\"container\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"a3366ea\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"663\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-663x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-663x1024.jpg 663w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-194x300.jpg 194w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-768x1187.jpg 768w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-994x1536.jpg 994w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist-1325x2048.jpg 1325w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/resist.jpg 1650w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 663px) 100vw, 663px\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"af6d71b\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eWhat do the struggles of the past teach us about the urgent challenges in our own time? \u003cem\u003eResist\u003c/em\u003e chronicles the inspiring story of young Black activists who have fought tirelessly at the helm for justice over the last century, from the 1920s to the Trayvon generation—how they reshaped America, left an indelible mark on history, and pave the way for the crucial work that must be done today.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/1250290988?tag=macmillan-20\"\u003eAmazon\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/resist-rita-omokha/1144473448?ean=9781250290984\u0026amp;st=AFF\u0026amp;2sid=Holtzbrinck%20Publishing%20Holdings,%20LP_7992675_NA\u0026amp;sourceId=AFFHoltzbrinck%20Publishing%20Holdings,%20LP\"\u003eB\u0026amp;N\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://bookshop.org/p/books/resist-how-a-century-of-young-black-activists-shaped-america-rita-omokha/20981915?ean=9781250290984\u0026amp;next=t\u0026amp;affiliate=3214\"\u003eBookshop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"ad2c582\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3\u003e\u003ci\u003eAfricatown\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"a54cd60\" data-element_type=\"container\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"17d3dd7\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" width=\"674\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-674x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-674x1024.jpg 674w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-197x300.jpg 197w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-768x1167.jpg 768w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-1011x1536.jpg 1011w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-1347x2048.jpg 1347w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Africatown-scaled.jpg 1684w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"2ea1a73\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eAn evocative and epic story, Nick Tabor’s \u003cem\u003eAfricatown\u003c/em\u003e charts the fraught history of America from those who were brought here as slaves but nevertheless established a home for themselves and their descendants, a community which often thrived despite persistent racism and environmental pollution.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/1250766540?tag=macmillan-20\"\u003eAmazon\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/africatown-nick-tabor/1141460159?ean=9781250766540\u0026amp;st=AFF\u0026amp;2sid=Holtzbrinck%20Publishing%20Holdings,%20LP_7992675_NA\u0026amp;sourceId=AFFHoltzbrinck%20Publishing%20Holdings,%20LP\"\u003eB\u0026amp;N\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://bookshop.org/p/books/africatown-america-s-last-slave-ship-and-the-community-it-created/18947828?ean=9781250766540\u0026amp;next=t\u0026amp;affiliate=3214\"\u003eBookshop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"19ed8ba\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3\u003e\u003ci\u003eBuses Are a Comin\u0026#39;\u003cspan\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"151c6ff\" data-element_type=\"container\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"d5ee546\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Buses-Are-a-Comin-by-Charles-Person.jpg\" title=\"\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"21b97dc\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eA firsthand exploration of the cost of boarding the bus of change to move America forward—written by one of the Civil Rights Movement’s pioneers.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/125083676X?tag=macmillan-20\"\u003eAmazon\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/buses-are-a-comin-charles-person/1136846526?ean=9781250836762\"\u003eB\u0026amp;N\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://bookshop.org/p/books/buses-are-a-comin-memoir-of-a-freedom-rider-charles-person/14623491?ean=9781250836762\u0026amp;next=t\u0026amp;affiliate=3214\"\u003eBookshop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"fe52800\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003ch3\u003e\u003ci\u003eThe Burning\u003c/i\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"4a85ecc\" data-element_type=\"container\"\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"8060c43\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"image.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"667\" height=\"1024\" src=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-667x1024.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-667x1024.jpg 667w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-196x300.jpg 196w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-768x1178.jpg 768w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-1001x1536.jpg 1001w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning-1335x2048.jpg 1335w, https://www.thehistoryreader.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/The-Burning.jpg 1613w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 667px) 100vw, 667px\"/\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\u003cdiv data-id=\"b91360e\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\"\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eAn unflinching account of America’s most horrific racial massacre, \u003cem\u003eThe Burning\u003c/em\u003e is essential reading as America finally comes to terms with its racial past.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cb\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/1250800722?tag=macmillan-20\"\u003eAmazon\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://www.barnesandnoble.com/w/the-burning-tim-madigan/1137370582?ean=9781250800725\"\u003eB\u0026amp;N\u003c/a\u003e | \u003ca href=\"https://bookshop.org/p/books/the-burning-the-tulsa-race-massacre-of-1921-tim-madigan/16649840?ean=9781250800725\u0026amp;next=t\u0026amp;affiliate=3214\"\u003eBookshop\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/b\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\n\t\t\t\t\t\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
